---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import RelatedTools from '../../../components/RelatedTools.astro';

// Tool metadata
const name = "Currency Converter";
const category = "finance";
const tier = "Finance & Tax";

// On-page SEO metadata
const pageTitle = "Currency Converter - Free Currency Exchange Calculator & App";
const description = "Free currency converter and currency exchange calculator. Convert euro to usd, track foreign currency exchange rates, and compare currencies with the best currency converter app.";
const canonicalUrl = "https://toolkify.com/tools/finance/currency-converter";
const ogImage = "/og/currency-converter.png";
const keywords = "currency converter, currency converter calculator, currency converter app, currency converter euro to usd, currency converter to usd, foreign currency converter, currency exchange rate, currency exchange calculator, currency exchange, best currency converter app";
---

<Layout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={description}
  toolName={name}
  toolCategory={category}
  keywords={keywords}
  canonical={canonicalUrl}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="website"
  hideBanner={true}
>
  <!-- SEO JSON-LD Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "Currency Converter",
      "alternateName": "Offline Currency Exchange Rate Calculator",
      "url": "https://toolkify.com/tools/finance/currency-converter",
      "description": "Calculate exchange rates instantly on your device with static, local conversion tables. Features bidirectional conversions, comparison list, and custom favorite pairs.",
      "applicationCategory": "FinanceApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "All",
      "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript. Requires HTML5.",
      "featureList": [
        "Bidirectional live currency conversions",
        "Over 25+ major world currencies supported",
        "Save default favorites to local storage",
        "Copy formatted outputs",
        "Full static rate reference table",
        "Offline privacy-first client-side calculation"
      ],
      "offers": {
        "@type": "Offer",
        "price": "0.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD"
      }
    }
  </script>

  <!-- Breadcrumb Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": 1,
          "name": "Home",
          "item": "https://toolkify.com/"
        },
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": 2,
          "name": "Finance & Tax Tools",
          "item": "https://toolkify.com/#finance"
        },
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": 3,
          "name": "Currency Converter",
          "item": "https://toolkify.com/tools/finance/currency-converter"
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>

  <!-- FAQ Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is a currency converter",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A currency converter is a digital application or tool designed to calculate the relative value of one country's currency against another's. It uses current exchange rates to compute the converted amount based on your inputs.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the best currency converter app",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The best currency converter app is one that is fast, accessible offline, privacy-focused, and free of intrusive ads. Our web-based currency converter app runs entirely client-side, meaning your calculation requests are processed directly on your device. This makes it an ideal option for secure, instant conversions without data tracking or lag.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "can to us currency converter",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A 'Can to US' currency converter refers to a Canadian Dollar (CAD) to United States Dollar (USD) exchange tool. To convert Canadian Dollars (CAD) to US Dollars (USD), you multiply the Canadian dollar amount by the current CAD/USD exchange rate. Our converter supports bidirectional CAD to USD conversions instantly.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the best currency converter tool",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The best currency converter tool is one that combines simple inputs, instant results, and reference tables for major global currencies like USD, EUR, GBP, JPY, and CAD. Features like custom favorite pairs, preset amount chips, and an offline mode make a tool highly practical for daily budgeting and quick calculations.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the best free currency converter app",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The best free currency converter app is a lightweight, responsive web application that requires no installation or registration. Our tool is 100% free, has no hidden fees, and doesn't require sharing personal financial data, making it highly secure and convenient for any desktop or mobile device.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the most accurate currency converter",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The most accurate currency converter depends on your needs. For real-time trading or bank transfers, live rates directly from interbank feeds are required. For planning, general travel budgeting, or offline estimation, a static converter with recent reference rates offers the most stable and reliable calculations without requiring constant internet access.</p>"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>

  <section
    class="max-w-[840px] w-full mx-auto px-4 py-3 sm:py-6 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:gap-4 animate-fade-in-up pb-16 print:p-0"
  >
    <!-- Breadcrumb & Header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 print:hidden">
      <nav
        class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate uppercase"
        aria-label="Breadcrumb"
      >
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Tools</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-brand-blue capitalize">{category}</span>
      </nav>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between mt-0.5 gap-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <h1 class="font-display font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl tracking-tight text-primary">
            {name}
          </h1>
          <span class="bg-surface-pricing-featured text-brand-blue text-[10px] py-0.5 px-2 rounded-full font-semibold uppercase whitespace-nowrap shrink-0">
            {tier}
          </span>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <button
            type="button"
            id="share-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Share tool link"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.684 10.742l5.028-2.513m0 7.544l-5.028-2.513M18 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm-6 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 0a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
            </svg>
            <span>Share</span>
          </button>

          <!-- Reset button pulled verbatim from json-formatter.astro -->
          <button
            type="button"
            id="reset-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-brand-coral hover:border-brand-coral rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Reset inputs and output"
          >
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              class="w-3.5 h-3.5"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 1121.21 7.89M9 11l3-3 3 3m-3-3v12"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            <span>Reset</span>
          </button>

          <!-- How it works button pulled verbatim from json-formatter.astro -->
          <button
            type="button"
            id="how-it-works-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="How currency converter works"
          >
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              class="w-3.5 h-3.5"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            <span>How it works</span>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Workspace Container (Zero-Scroll Compact Layout) -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 items-stretch">
      
      <!-- Left Column: Converter Core (Desktop: 7/12 width) -->
      <div class="md:col-span-7 flex flex-col gap-3">
        <div class="card-base p-4 sm:p-5 flex flex-col gap-4 relative">
          
          <!-- Conversion Box Pair -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 relative">
            
            <!-- From Amount & Currency -->
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
              <label for="from-amount" class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-charcoal flex justify-between">
                <span>From Amount</span>
                <span id="from-label" class="text-stone">Source Currency</span>
              </label>
              <div class="flex gap-2 relative">
                <!-- Currency Button -->
                <button
                  type="button"
                  id="from-currency-btn"
                  class="flex items-center justify-between gap-1.5 px-3 py-2 bg-surface hover:bg-canvas border border-hairline-strong rounded-md text-sm font-semibold text-primary transition-all cursor-pointer w-32 select-none"
                  aria-haspopup="listbox"
                  aria-label="Source Currency"
                >
                  <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
                    <span id="from-flag" class="text-base select-none">🇺🇸</span>
                    <span id="from-code" class="font-mono">USD</span>
                  </span>
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3 h-3 text-stone" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                  </svg>
                </button>

                <!-- Decimal Input -->
                <div class="relative flex-grow">
                  <span id="from-symbol" class="absolute left-3 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-sm font-semibold select-none">$</span>
                  <input
                    type="number"
                    id="from-amount"
                    value="100"
                    step="any"
                    class="text-input w-full pl-7 pr-3 text-sm font-mono"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                    placeholder="0.00"
                    autocomplete="off"
                  />
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Absolute Swap Button Overlay in between -->
            <div class="flex justify-center -my-1.5 z-10">
              <button
                type="button"
                id="swap-btn"
                class="w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline-strong text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle active:scale-95"
                title="Swap currencies and amounts"
                aria-label="Swap Currencies"
              >
                <svg
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  id="swap-icon"
                  class="w-4 h-4 transition-transform duration-300"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  stroke-width="2"
                >
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M7 16V4m0 0L3 8m4-4l4 4m6 0v12m0 0l4-4m-4 4l-4-4" />
                </svg>
              </button>
            </div>

            <!-- To Amount & Currency -->
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
              <label for="to-amount" class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-charcoal flex justify-between">
                <span>To Amount</span>
                <span id="to-label" class="text-stone">Target Currency</span>
              </label>
              <div class="flex gap-2 relative">
                <!-- Currency Button -->
                <button
                  type="button"
                  id="to-currency-btn"
                  class="flex items-center justify-between gap-1.5 px-3 py-2 bg-surface hover:bg-canvas border border-hairline-strong rounded-md text-sm font-semibold text-primary transition-all cursor-pointer w-32 select-none"
                  aria-haspopup="listbox"
                  aria-label="Target Currency"
                >
                  <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
                    <span id="to-flag" class="text-base select-none">🇪🇺</span>
                    <span id="to-code" class="font-mono">EUR</span>
                  </span>
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3 h-3 text-stone" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                  </svg>
                </button>

                <!-- Decimal Input -->
                <div class="relative flex-grow">
                  <span id="to-symbol" class="absolute left-3 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-sm font-semibold select-none">€</span>
                  <input
                    type="number"
                    id="to-amount"
                    value="91.74"
                    step="any"
                    class="text-input w-full pl-7 pr-3 text-sm font-mono"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                    placeholder="0.00"
                    autocomplete="off"
                  />
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>

          <!-- Currency Picker Floating Popover (Shared for both sides) -->
          <div
            id="currency-picker"
            class="absolute top-1/2 left-4 right-4 -translate-y-1/2 bg-canvas border border-hairline-strong rounded-xl shadow-modal z-50 p-3 hidden flex flex-col gap-2 animate-scale-in"
            style="max-height: 280px;"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 pb-1 border-b border-hairline">
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-primary flex-grow">Select Currency</span>
              <button type="button" id="close-picker-btn" class="text-stone hover:text-primary transition-colors text-xs font-bold px-1.5 cursor-pointer">✕</button>
            </div>
            <input
              type="text"
              id="picker-search"
              class="text-input text-xs h-9 py-1 px-2.5 w-full bg-surface"
              placeholder="Search by code, name, or country..."
              autocomplete="off"
            />
            <div id="picker-list" class="flex flex-col gap-0.5 overflow-y-auto flex-grow text-xs pr-1">
              <!-- Dynamically populated list items -->
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Preset Chips & Quick Actions -->
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-3 pt-1 border-t border-hairline-soft mt-1">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1">
              <span class="text-[10px] text-stone font-semibold mr-1">Presets:</span>
              {
                [100, 500, 1000, 5000].map((amt) => (
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="preset-chip text-[11px] font-semibold px-2 py-0.5 bg-surface hover:bg-hairline rounded border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary transition-all cursor-pointer active:scale-95"
                    data-amount={amt}
                  >
                    {amt}
                  </button>
                ))
              }
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <button
                type="button"
                id="favorite-btn"
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer"
                title="Save current pair as default"
              >
                <span id="favorite-icon">☆</span>
                <span id="favorite-text">Set Default</span>
              </button>
              <button
                type="button"
                id="copy-btn"
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-brand-blue rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer"
                title="Copy conversion text to clipboard"
              >
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8 5H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-1M8 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M8 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M8 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m0 0h2a2 2 0 012 2v3m2 4H10m0 0l3-3m-3 3l3 3" />
                </svg>
                <span>Copy</span>
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- HONESTY REQUIREMENT: Static Rates Disclaimer -->
        <div class="bg-surface border border-hairline-strong rounded-lg p-2.5 text-[11px] text-slate flex flex-col gap-1 leading-normal select-none">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between font-bold text-primary">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-1 text-brand-blue">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
              </svg>
              Static Local Exchange Rates
            </span>
            <span id="rates-date-label">July 5, 2026</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This tool uses fixed, bundled offline rates. These figures are for general reference and rough estimation only. Do <strong>NOT</strong> use for actual bank transfers, live foreign exchange transactions, travel money exchanges, or stock/currency trading.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column: Secondary Side Panel (Desktop: 5/12 width) -->
      <div class="md:col-span-5 flex flex-col gap-3">
        <div class="card-base p-3 flex flex-col gap-3 h-full justify-between">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            <!-- Tabs Header -->
            <div class="flex rounded-full bg-surface p-0.5 border border-hairline w-full">
              <button
                type="button"
                id="tab-compare-btn"
                class="flex-1 text-center text-[11px] py-1 rounded-full font-bold transition-all cursor-pointer bg-primary text-canvas"
              >
                Compare Currencies
              </button>
              <button
                type="button"
                id="tab-table-btn"
                class="flex-1 text-center text-[11px] py-1 rounded-full font-semibold transition-all cursor-pointer text-slate hover:text-primary"
              >
                Rate Tables
              </button>
            </div>

            <!-- Compare Tab Content -->
            <div id="tab-compare-content" class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-[10px] text-stone font-semibold px-1">
                <span>CONVERSION SUMMARY</span>
                <span id="compare-base-amount" class="font-mono">100.00 USD</span>
              </div>
              <div id="compare-list" class="flex flex-col gap-1 overflow-y-auto max-h-[170px] pr-1">
                <!-- Comparison entries will be generated here -->
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Rate Table Tab Content (Hidden by default) -->
            <div id="tab-table-content" class="flex flex-col gap-1.5 hidden">
              <div class="relative">
                <input
                  type="text"
                  id="table-search"
                  class="text-input text-[11px] h-8 py-1 px-2.5 w-full bg-surface"
                  placeholder="Filter rates by name/code..."
                  autocomplete="off"
                />
              </div>
              <div id="rate-table-list" class="flex flex-col gap-1 overflow-y-auto max-h-[140px] pr-1 text-xs">
                <!-- Bundled rates rows relative to USD -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Bottom micro status row -->
          <div class="border-t border-hairline-soft pt-1.5 flex items-center justify-between text-[9px] text-stone">
            <span>Offline Enabled</span>
            <span>Local calculations</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <RelatedTools currentSlug="currency-converter" />

    <!-- Below the Fold Details / Education (Strict Separator) -->
    <div class="border-t border-hairline pt-6 mt-4 max-w-[760px] mx-auto text-slate flex flex-col gap-8">
      <article class="prose max-w-none text-xs leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-4 text-slate">
        <h2 class="font-display font-medium text-lg text-primary">About Offline Currency Conversion</h2>
        <p>
          Unlike tools that query remote APIs, this Currency Converter runs completely on your local device. The conversion table represents standard median global exchange rates static as of July 5, 2026. This allows for rapid calculations when exploring financial estimations without sending data across networks or running into offline errors.
        </p>
        <p>
          To maintain accurate math when switching currencies (for example, JPY to EUR), this tool uses strict cross-multiplication via a USD base index: 
          <code class="bg-surface px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono">Amount(To) = Amount(From) * [Rate(To) / Rate(From)]</code>.
          This ensures zero statistical drift and respects the formal fractional differences between various fiat models.
        </p>
      </article>

      <!-- 600+ Word SEO Content Block -->
      <article class="prose max-w-none text-xs leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-4 text-slate border-t border-hairline pt-6">
        <h2 class="font-display font-medium text-lg text-primary">
          Comprehensive Guide to Currency Converters & Foreign Exchange Calculations
        </h2>
        <p>
          In today’s highly interconnected global economy, keeping track of fluctuating currency values is essential. Whether you are an international traveler budgeting for an upcoming trip, an e-commerce entrepreneur pricing goods for global markets, or a financial enthusiast tracking market trends, a reliable <strong>currency converter</strong> is an indispensable utility. Understanding the mechanics of foreign exchange and having access to a high-quality <strong>currency converter calculator</strong> can save you significant time and money.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display font-medium text-sm text-primary mt-2">What is a Currency Converter?</h3>
        <p>
          A <strong>currency converter</strong> is a digital application or tool designed to calculate the relative value of one country’s currency against another’s. At its core, the tool performs simple multiplication and division based on a specific <strong>currency exchange rate</strong>. For example, when you want to convert money, a dedicated <strong>currency converter euro to usd</strong> takes the base amount in Euros (EUR) and multiplies it by the current conversion rate to output the equivalent value in United States Dollars (USD).
        </p>
        <p>
          Using a web-based <strong>currency converter app</strong> allows you to perform these calculations instantly on any device. Rather than performing manual arithmetic or searching for conversion formulas, you simply input the amount, select your desired currency pair, and view the results in real time. If you primarily deal with American markets, setting your default parameters to act as a <strong>currency converter to usd</strong> ensures that you can see standard values instantly.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display font-medium text-sm text-primary mt-2">The Mechanics of Currency Exchange Rates</h3>
        <p>
          A <strong>currency exchange rate</strong> is the price of one nation's currency in terms of another currency. Rates are determined by the global foreign exchange (Forex) market, where trillions of dollars are traded daily by banks, governments, corporations, and individual traders. These rates fluctuate constantly throughout the day due to various economic indicators, including interest rates, inflation, geopolitical stability, and trade balance.
        </p>
        <p>
          To make these fluctuations easy to understand, a <strong>foreign currency converter</strong> references a base index (often USD) and calculates cross-currency values. For instance, to calculate JPY to EUR, the calculator uses the formula: <code class="bg-surface px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono">Amount(EUR) = Amount(JPY) * (Rate(EUR) / Rate(JPY))</code>. This ensures that all conversions remain mathematically consistent.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display font-medium text-sm text-primary mt-2">Why Use a Digital Currency Exchange Calculator?</h3>
        <p>
          Manual conversion can lead to errors, especially when dealing with multiple currencies or complex fractional values. A digital <strong>currency exchange calculator</strong> simplifies the process by handling the math on your behalf. Additionally, premium web applications provide valuable features such as interactive preset chips, dynamic comparison tables, and bidirectional inputs that let you update either side of the calculation seamlessly.
        </p>

